      "comment_id" : 56807956,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "I&#39;m not sure off the top of my head. If it&#39;s only space, you can form your own class by bracketing it, so in your case probably (note, this is untested)  <code>[ +\\\\-&#47;;]+</code> - notice the <code>\\` around the </code>-` to escape it. Now, this will probably match <code>This is+a+ - + - + - test</code> into 4 tokens, which may or may not be desired. The real problem is you can&#39;t use <code>\\\\s</code> to match &quot;any whitespace&quot;. You might be better off not using split, and just using <code>Matcher m = Pattern.compile(&quot;([A-Za-z0-9]+)&quot;).matcher(text); while(m.find()) list.add(m.group(1));</code> to fetch words instead of splitting a big text."
