    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Since it's been a while since these answers were posted, here's another more current way to do what's asked:</p>\n\n<pre><code>List&lt;String&gt; output = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();\ntry (Scanner sc = new Scanner(inputString)) {\n    while (sc.hasNext()) output.add(sc.next());\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Now you have a list of strings (which is arguably better than an array); if you do need an array, you can do <code>output.toArray(new String[0]);</code></p>\n"
